Execution Version
SHARED TRANSMISSION FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS SHARED TRANSMISSION FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”), is entered into as of October 31, 2018, by and among Minco IV & V Interconnection, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Minco Interconnection”), Minco Wind III, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Minco III”), Minco Wind IV, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Minco IV”) and Minco Wind V, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Minco V”, jointly with Minco Interconnection, Minco III and Minco IV, the “Parties” and each a “Party”, and, jointly with Minco III and Minco IV, the “Project Owners” and each a “Project Owner”). RECITALS WHEREAS, Minco III owns and operates a wind energy generation facility with a capacity of 100.8 MW (the “Minco III Project”); WHEREAS, Minco IV is developing, and upon completion, will own and operate a wind energy generation facility with an expected nameplate capacity of 130 MW (the “Minco IV Project”); WHEREAS, Minco V is developing, and upon completion, will own and operate a wind energy generation facility with an expected nameplate capacity of 220 MW (the “Minco V Project”, jointly with the Minco III Project and the Minco IV Project, the “Projects” and each a “Project”); WHEREAS, Minco III is a party to that certain Interconnection Agreement, dated February 29, 2012 (the “Minco III IA”), among Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (“SPP”), Oklahoma Gas and Electric Company (“OG&E”) and Minco III pursuant to which Minco III has the right to receive certain services as detailed in the Minco III IA for the full capacity of the Minco III Project; WHEREAS, Minco Interconnection is a party to that certain Generation Interconnection Agreement, dated October 23, 2018 (the “Minco Interconnection GIA,” the Minco Interconnection GIA and the Minco III IA, individually an “Interconnection Agreement,” and jointly, the “Interconnection Agreements”), among SPP, OG&E and Minco Interconnection, through which Minco Interconnection will provide to Minco IV and Minco V interconnection service; WHEREAS, Minco Interconnection owns or will own certain personal property, fixtures, equipment and/or facilities described in Exhibit A attached hereto (the “Minco Shared Facilities”) that are necessary for the interconnection of each Project; WHEREAS, Minco Interconnection also owns or will own certain personal property, fixtures, equipment and/or facilities described in Exhibit B attached hereto (the “Minco IV and V Shared Facilities” and, together with the Minco Shared Facilities, the “Shared Facilities”) that are necessary for the interconnection of the Minco IV Project and the Minco V Project; and WHEREAS, Minco Interconnection wishes to grant each of Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V the right to use the Minco Shared Facilities, and to each of Minco IV and Minco V the right to use the Minco IV and Minco V Shared Facilities, in each case, as set forth herein for the operation of its respective Project subject to certain conditions and obligations in respect thereof as set forth herein. NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows: AGREEMENT TERM; EARLY TERMINATION Term. The term of this Agreement shall commence on the date first written above and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties, or (b) pursuant to Section 1.2 of this Agreement. Early Termination. This Agreement shall automatically terminate, without further action by any Party and without further liability of any Party to any other Party, upon the date that Minco III, Minco IV, and Minco V, or their successors and assigns, shall have permanently ceased operation of the Projects for the production of electric energy. If only one of Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V ceases operations of its respective Project, the remaining Parties shall act in good faith to amend and restate this Agreement to continue this Agreement as between only such Parties on terms substantively similar to this Agreement. GRANT OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS AND SHARING OF INTERCONNECTION SERVICE Grant. (a) Minco Interconnection hereby grants to Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V, respectively, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Minco Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with the ownership, operation and maintenance of the Minco III Project, Minco IV Project and the Minco V Project, respectively. Each of Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V, respectively, hereby grants to Minco Interconnection during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access any roads as may be reasonably necessary in connection with obtaining access to the Minco Shared Facilities (and shall include the right of any employee, agent or contractor of Minco Interconnection to access such roads). Furthermore, Minco IV hereby grants to Minco Interconnection, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Operations and Maintenance Building and warehouse owned by Minco IV as may be reasonably necessary in connection with Minco Interconnection’s ownership, operation and maintenance of the Shared Facilities. (b) Minco Interconnection hereby grants to Minco IV and Minco V, respectively, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with the ownership, operation and maintenance of the Minco IV Project and the Minco V Project, respectively. Each of Minco IV and Minco V, respectively, hereby grants to Minco Interconnection during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access any roads as may be reasonably necessary in connection with obtaining access to the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities (and shall include the right of any employee, agent or contractor of Minco Interconnection to access such roads). Essential Nature. Minco Interconnection hereby acknowledges that the right of Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V to access and utilize the Minco Shared Facilities is essential to the production of electric energy by the Minco III Project, Minco IV Project and the Minco V Project, respectively, and to the delivery of such energy to the transmission system. Minco Interconnection also hereby acknowledges that the right of Minco IV and Minco V to access and utilize the Minco IV and Minco V Shared Facilities is essential to the production of electric energy by the Minco IV Project and the Minco V Project, respectively, and to the delivery of such energy to the transmission system. Vesting. The right to access and utilize the Minco Shared Facilities granted hereunder by Minco Interconnection to Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V shall vest in each of Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V, respectively, as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title, leasehold or other interest or rights in the Minco Shared Facilities. The right to access and utilize the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities granted hereunder by Minco Interconnection to Minco IV and Minco V shall vest in each of Minco IV and Minco V, respectively, as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title, leasehold or other interest or rights in the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities Sharing of Interconnection Service. Of the 350 MW of capacity available under the Minco Interconnection GIA, Minco Interconnection shall provide 130 MW for interconnection and operation of the Minco IV Project and 220 MW for interconnection and operation of the Minco V Project. Minco Interconnection shall provide certain services to Minco IV and Minco V consisting of those services Minco Interconnection receives under the Minco Interconnection GIA, as necessary to enable the energy generating by Minco IV and Minco V, respectively, to reach the point of interconnection with OG&E. NATURE OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS Limitation on Grant. Subject to Section 3.3 hereof, (a) the grant of rights under this Agreement by Minco Interconnection to Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V is made only to the extent that such rights do not limit in any material respect the ability of Minco Interconnection to comply with the terms and conditions of the Minco Interconnection GIA and (b) the grant of rights under this Agreement by Minco IV is made only to the extent that such rights do not limit in any material respect the ability of Minco IV to utilize the Operations and Maintenance Building and warehouse owned by Minco IV in the manner required for the prudent operation of the Minco IV Project. For the avoidance of doubt, the grant of rights under this Agreement by Minco Interconnection to Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V shall not relieve Minco Interconnection of its obligations under the Minco Interconnection GIA. Assignment or Transfer of Rights. Except as set forth in Section 9.6 hereof, Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V shall not assign or transfer any rights granted to such Party hereunder with regard to the Shared Facilities, or grant any permission, license, right of way or similar right with regard to the Shared Facilities, without the prior written consent of Minco Interconnection. Interference. Subject to the terms of this Agreement, in no event shall any Party be entitled to exercise its rights to access and utilize the Shared Facilities if the exercise of such rights would materially interfere with, or limit the reasonable and necessary access and utilization of, the Shared Facilities by any other Party or inhibit (a) Minco III’s ability to comply with the terms of the Minco III IA or (b) Minco Interconnection’s ability to comply with the terms of the Minco Interconnection GIA. Prior Written Consent. Except as set forth in this Agreement, Minco Interconnection shall not take any action that results in the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of the respective rights or increases the obligations or responsibilities of Minco III, Minco IV or Minco V of access to, utilization of or reliance upon the Shared Facilities, as applicable, without the prior written consent of Minco III, Minco IV or Minco V, respectively. MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES Allocation of Certain Costs and Expenses. Subject to Section 4.1(ii) and Section 6.4 hereof, Minco Interconnection shall be responsible for the ownership or possession, operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities. Minco Interconnection has engaged or will engage NextEra Energy Operating Services, LLC (the “Operator”') pursuant to an operation and maintenance agreement entered into or to be entered into by and between Minco Interconnection and Operator (the “O&M Agreement”) to perform the Services (as defined therein) for the Shared Facilities. Subject to Section 6.4 hereof, each of Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V agrees that all Reimbursable Costs (as defined in the O&M Agreement), the Operating Fee (as defined in the O&M Agreement), and all other costs, expenses, penalties, and liabilities of any kind with respect to the Shared Facilities (regardless of whether or not any such costs, expenses, penalties, or liabilities are incurred in connection with the O&M Agreement, are payable to the Operator or a third party, or otherwise) (collectively, “Shared Facilities Costs”) of Minco Interconnection, including, without limitation, real property taxes, shall be allocated in accordance with their respective pro rata share, which as of any date of determination, shall be equal to a fraction, the numerator of which shall be the contract capacity in respect of a Project, and the denominator of which shall be the aggregate contract capacity in respect of all of the Projects (the “Pro Rata Share”). Each of Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V shall make its respective portion of any payment due and payable by it hereunder to Minco Interconnection with respect to any Shared Facilities Costs, in a time and manner that will allow Minco Interconnection to comply with its payment obligations under the O&M Agreement or otherwise. Minco Interconnection shall submit monthly invoices in amounts to Minco III, Minco IV and Minco IV for such costs and expenses and Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V shall pay Minco Interconnection on or before the 5th calendar day of the month following receipt of such invoice or, if such day is not a business day, on the next succeeding business day. Any payment for retail station power service shall be the responsibility of Minco III, Minco IV or Minco V, as applicable. Solely in connection with the Services performed on the Shared Facilities, Minco Interconnection agrees to pursue all available remedies against the Operator available to it under the O&M Agreement as may be commercially reasonable. Subject to Section 6.4 hereof, the receipt of any payments for liability incurred by the Operator under the O&M Agreement with respect to the Services performed on the Shared Facilities shall be allocated based on the Pro Rata Share and Minco Interconnection shall make a payment to Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V for such allocations as soon as reasonably practical following receipt of such liability payments from the Operator. 4.2 Successor Agreement. In the event that the Projects and the Shared Facilities are no longer operated and maintained by a single entity for any reason, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement) that specifies the division of responsibilities of the entities providing operation and maintenance services associated with the Shared Facilities. CHANGE IN LAW Change in Law. In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Shared Facilities, any of the Projects, or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement. If, despite the use of good faith efforts, the Parties are unable to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms, Minco Interconnection shall be deemed to have authorization to determine on behalf of all Parties such amendment, modification or replacement as is appropriate and consistent with prudent industry standards, each Interconnection Agreement and Applicable Law, and each other Party shall enter into any amendment, modification or replacement proposed by Minco Interconnection. CERTAIN COVENANTS Authority and Operational Abilities. Each of the Parties represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement. Payment of Certain Studies, Upgrades and Facilities. In the event that any Party at any time shall have paid, funded or posted as security pursuant to an Interconnection Agreement any amounts required under such Interconnection Agreement for facility upgrades or studies to the extent arising as a result of the interconnection of any other Party’s Project and required under the applicable Interconnection Agreement, such other Party shall promptly, on demand, either post alternative security, or pay or reimburse the amounts paid or funded to the Party that initially paid, funded or posted such security. Observance of the Interconnection Agreements. Minco Interconnection shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement and the Minco Interconnection GIA in a manner that is reasonable and not discriminatory against the other Parties. Each of Minco IV and Minco V shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is reasonable and not discriminatory against the other Parties. Minco III shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement and the Minco III IA in a manner that is reasonable and not discriminatory against the other Parties. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement: Minco III, Minco IV, and Minco V each agree to operate its respective Project in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in its the Interconnection Agreement through which it directly (in the case of Minco III) or indirectly (in the case of Minco IV and Minco V) receives interconnection service, and in a manner consistent with the terms of its respective Interconnection Agreement. Minco IV and Minco V each agree to observe and facilitate Minco Interconnection's compliance with all provisions of the Minco Interconnection GIA to which Minco Interconnection is subject (and all insurance requirements, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof) as it relates to its respective Project. Minco III, Minco IV, and Minco V each agree to assume and be bound by all obligations related to its respective rights to receive interconnection service, directly or indirectly, as set forth in its applicable Interconnection Agreement. Minco III, Minco IV, and Minco V each agree to not take any action (or refrain from taking any action) which would result in a breach of the applicable Interconnection Agreement. Minco III, Minco IV, and Minco V each agree to use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of its respective Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default under the applicable Interconnection Agreement, and if such default occurs, to promptly cure such default in accordance with the terms of the applicable Interconnection Agreement. Minco IV and Minco V each agree to comply with all instructions, as may be communicated by Minco Interconnection, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the Minco Interconnection GIA with respect to its respective Project. Minco III, Minco IV, and Minco V each agree to provide each other Party with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of its respective Project required for each other Party to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the applicable Interconnection Agreement. All Parties agree to provide to each other Party copies of all material notices and instructions received by any Party under the applicable Interconnection Agreement. Adjustments to Cost Allocations; Decommissioning. If an operational issue arises at one of the Projects that could be reasonably expected to result in a material breach by Minco Interconnection of the Minco Interconnection GIA, by Minco III of the Minco III IA or by any Party under this Agreement (an “Adverse Event”), Minco Interconnection shall curtail the Project that is causing the Adverse Event, or if the Minco III Project is causing the Adverse Event, Minco III shall curtail its Project. In the event of such curtailment, the Project that has caused the Adverse Event shall not be permitted to deliver energy to the Shared Facilities until such time as the Adverse Event has been cured to the reasonable satisfaction of Minco Interconnection. If, as a direct result of an Adverse Event, Minco Interconnection incurs any Shared Facilities Costs, the Project that has caused such Adverse Event shall be solely responsible for reimbursing Minco Interconnection for any such Shared Facilities Costs. In the event that two or more Projects are responsible for the Adverse Event, and to the extent that Minco Interconnection, in its sole and absolute discretion, can accurately allocate responsibility for such Adverse Event between the Projects, each Project shall be responsible for its allocable portion of the applicable Shared Facilities Costs. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for Minco Interconnection, as determined in its sole and absolute discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility, each Project responsible for the Adverse Event will be liable for its respective Pro Rata Share of such Shared Facilities Costs (provided that, for this purpose, the denominator used in determining the Pro Rata Share shall be the aggregate capacity of the Projects responsible for the Adverse Event only). Notwithstanding any contrary provision contained herein or the O&M Agreement, if any Shared Facilities Costs are incurred by Minco Interconnection, and Minco Interconnection reasonably determines that such Shared Facilities Costs (a) would not have been incurred in the absence of the development, construction, operation, or maintenance of the Minco IV Project or the Minco V Project, (b) are not necessary or prudent for the continuing operations of the Minco III Project, or (c) are primarily incurred with respect to the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities, then Minco III shall have no responsibility for any portion of such Shared Facilities Costs. Subject to Section 6.4(iii) hereof, but notwithstanding any other provision contained herein or the O&M Agreement, if any Shared Facilities Costs are incurred by Minco Interconnection, which Shared Facilities Costs Minco Interconnection reasonably determines are incurred primarily to benefit the Minco IV Project and/or the Minco V Project or primarily with respect to the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities, then, to the extent Minco Interconnection, in its sole and absolute discretion, can accurately allocate responsibility for such Shared Facilities Costs between the Minco IV Project and the Minco V Project, each of Minco IV and Minco V shall be responsible for its allocable portion of the applicable Shared Facilities Costs. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for Minco Interconnection, as determined in its sole and absolute discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility between Minco IV and Minco V (but Minco Interconnection reasonably determines that such Shared Facilities Costs are incurred primarily to benefit the Minco IV Project and the Minco V Project or primarily with respect to Minco IV and V Shared Facilities), then each of Minco IV and Minco V shall be liable for its respective Pro Rata Share of such Shared Facilities Costs (provided that, for this purpose, the denominator used in determining the Pro Rata Share shall be the aggregate capacity of the Minco IV Project and the Minco V Project only). At the end of the later of (a) the useful life of the Minco Shared Facilities, and (b) a time at which the Minco Shared Facilities are no longer required by any of the Projects (the “Termination of Transmission Activities”), the Project Owners shall, jointly and severally, within twelve (12) months of the Termination of Transmission Activities (the “Restoration Window”) take any and all actions required by any Law (as defined in the O&M Agreement), Government Agency (as defined in the O&M Agreement), or any reasonable requirement by any leasehold or easement grantor to remediate, mothball, decommission, take down, dismantle, and remove all Minco Shared Facilities, and related access roads, and fill up all holes caused by such removal and restore the surface of the real estate underneath the Minco Shared Facilities (the “Minco Shared Facilities Area”) to the same condition as the Minco Shared Facilities Area was prior to entry thereon and use thereof by the Project Owners; provided, however, Minco III shall have no obligation hereunder to take any such actions with respect to any portion of the Minco Shared Facilities or Minco Shared Facilities Area that, in the absence of the development, construction, operation, and maintenance of the Minco IV Project and/or the Minco V Project, would not constitute a portion of the original Minco III Project. At the end of the later of (a) the useful life of the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities, and (b) a time at which the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities are no longer required by either the Minco IV Project or the Minco V Project (the “Termination of Transmission Activities”), Minco IV and Minco V shall, jointly and severally, within twelve (12) months of the Termination of Transmission Activities (the “Restoration Window”) take any and all actions required by any Law (as defined in the O&M Agreement), Government Agency (as defined in the O&M Agreement), or any reasonable requirement by any leasehold or easement grantor to remediate, mothball, decommission, take down, dismantle, and remove all Minco IV and V Shared Facilities, and related access roads, and fill up all holes caused by such removal and restore the surface of the real estate underneath the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities (the “Minco IV and V Shared Facilities Area”) to the same condition as the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities Area was prior to entry thereon and use thereof by Minco IV and Minco V. For the avoidance of doubt, Minco III shall have no obligation hereunder to take any such actions with respect any portion of the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities or Minco IV and V Shared Facilities Area. Without limiting Section 9.7 hereof, in the event that any Project Owner is required to pay to any party any cost, expense, or liability, which cost, expense, or liability is allocable to another Project Owner pursuant to this Section 6.4, such responsible Project Owner(s) shall indemnify, defend and hold such paying Project Owner harmless from any and all such costs, expenses, or liabilities, including, without limitation, attorney fees. Curtailment. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, in the event of any occurrences related to (A) market conditions, the Transmission System (as defined in the Interconnection Agreements), OG&E’s grid or otherwise mandated (“External Curtailment”) and (B) the Projects or the Shared Facilities (“Internal Curtailment”) which require curtailments that affect deliveries to the grid of energy generated at the Projects for a period of time (the “Curtailment Period”), the Project Owners understand and agree that: (i) in the event of an External Curtailment or Internal Curtailment, Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (the “Transmission Provider”) or the Operator, as applicable, shall inform the Operator or the Transmission Provider, as applicable, of such External Curtailment or Internal Curtailment, including the particulars thereof, and (ii) each of the Transmission Provider and the Operator shall, during the Curtailment Period, coordinate their actions to curtail the Project Owners’ deliveries of energy to the extent required; it being understood that, to the extent any External Curtailment or Internal Curtailment is not specifically directed to any specific Project(s), the External Curtailment or Internal Curtailment shall be allocated among all Projects according to each Project’s Pro Rata Share. Agreement to Cooperate. Each Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with the other Parties so that, subject to the terms of this Agreement, each Project benefits from the full utilization and enjoyment of the Shared Facilities as is necessary for the efficient operation of each such Project; provided, however, that this Section 6.6 shall not be construed to create any affirmative obligations of Minco III with respect to the Minco IV and V Shared Facilities. No Liens. Each Party agrees not to grant any mortgages, liens, pledges, charges or security interests (collectively, “Liens”) on the Shared Facilities and to keep the Shared Facilities free and clear of all Liens by such Party other than: Liens for taxes which are either not yet delinquent or are subject to a good faith contest in which adequate reserves are established in accordance with GAAP with respect to the contested item (if and to the extent GAAP requires the establishment of such reserves); defects, restrictions, irregularities, encumbrances (other than for borrowed money) and clouds on title and statutory liens that do not materially impair the value or use of the Shared Facilities for the Projects; pledges to secure statutory obligations relating to worker's compensation and/or unemployment insurance or other social security legislation; carriers', warehousemen's, mechanics', workmen's, materialmen's, suppliers', construction or other similar Liens arising in the ordinary course of business of the Parties or incident to the construction, operation, repair, restoration or improvement of the Shared Facilities for obligations (A) which are not yet due or (B) which are the subject of a good faith contest in which adequate reserves are established in accordance with GAAP (if and to the extent GAAP requires the establishment of such reserves); and Liens arising out of judgments or awards in an amount less than $1,000,000 so long as (i) enforcement of any such Lien has been stayed and an appeal or proceeding for review is being prosecuted in good faith, and (ii) adequate reserves have been established in connection therewith in accordance with GAAP (if and to the extent GAAP requires the establishment of such reserves). MATERIAL BREACH Material Breach by any Party. In the event of any material breach of this Agreement by any Party and such Party's failure to cure such breach within a reasonable time not to exceed thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from any other Party describing such breach, such Party shall have the right, but not the obligation, in addition to all remedies available to it at law or in equity, to (i) cure the breach on behalf of the breaching Party, or (ii) suspend the breaching Party's access to all or any portion of the Shared Facilities owned by such non-breaching Party for so long as such default shall be continuing and remain uncured; provided, however, that in the event of any breach by a Party of this Agreement that may give rise to a breach by any other Party pursuant to the terms of its respective Interconnection Agreement, such Party shall not be required to provide the breaching Party hereunder with notice and/or an opportunity to cure in order to exercise the remedy specified in clause (i) or (ii) of this sentence only; and provided, further, that the remedy specified in clause (i) may be exercised, without prejudice to any right or remedy of any Party hereunder, by any lender or investor of such Party. If a Party (or any lender/investor thereof) chooses to cure a breaching Party's default, the breaching Party shall reimburse such Party (or such Party's lender/investor) upon demand for all commercially reasonable costs incurred by such Party (or such Party's lender/investor) in curing such breach. FORCE MAJEURE 8.1 Force Majeure. In the event of an act of God, government order or restraint, war (declared or undeclared) or warlike conditions, act of terrorism, blockade, revolution, strike, lockout, civil commotion, fire, flood, storm, epidemic or any other occurrence beyond a Party's reasonable control (each a “Force Majeure Event”), such Party shall promptly notify each other Party thereof and, so long as such condition shall persist, such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement caused directly or indirectly thereby. The claiming Party shall give each other Party notice describing the particulars of the Force Majeure Event. Within fifteen (15) days after giving notice of the Force Majeure Event, the claiming Party shall give each other Party an estimate of the Force Majeure Event's expected duration and probable impact. The claiming Party shall continue to furnish each other Party with timely regular reports during the continuation of the Force Majeure Event. Each Party shall immediately exercise commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit the impact to its obligations hereunder as a result of the Force Majeure Event. MISCELLANEOUS Relationship of Parties. The Parties do not intend to create any joint venture, partnership, association or any other entity for the conduct of any business. Nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize any Party to act on behalf of any other Party. Non-Interference. Subject to Section 3.3 hereof, each Party agrees not to interfere with the reasonable and necessary utilization of the Shared Facilities by any other Party as permitted hereunder. 9.3 Modification and Amendment. The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by all of the Parties, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld. 9.4 Waiver. The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party's right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect. 9.5 Enforceability. Any provision of this Agreement which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of such remaining provisions hereof. 9.6 Assignment. No Party may assign any of its benefits, rights or obligations hereunder to any third party without the prior written consent of each other Party, provided, however, that any Party may collaterally assign this Agreement to any entity, or such entity's agent, in connection with a financing or a refinancing of its respective Project. 9.7 Indemnification. Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold each other Party, its officers, directors, shareholders, members and affiliates, harmless from any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death to any person or damage to property, demand, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees, and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from the indemnifying Party's performance or nonperformance of its obligations under this Agreement, except in cases of gross negligence or intentional wrongdoing, by the indemnified party. However, in no event shall any Party be liable under any provision of this Agreement for any losses, damages, costs or expenses for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of profit or revenue, loss of the use of equipment, cost of capital, cost of temporary equipment or services, whether based in whole or in part in contract, in tort, including negligence, strict liability, or any other theory of liability; provided, however, that damages for which a Party may be liable to any other Party under another agreement will not be considered to be special, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages hereunder. Choice of Law, Jurisdiction and Waiver of Jury Trial. This Agreement and the rights and obligations of the Parties hereunder will be governed pursuant to, and enforced, construed and interpreted in accordance with, the laws of the State of New York without regard to principles of conflicts of laws (other than Section 5-1401 of the General Obligations Law of the State of New York). Venue for resolution of any disputes under this Agreement shall be New York County, New York. Each of the Parties irrevocably and unconditionally submits to the exclusive jurisdiction of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York .for the purposes of any suit, action or other proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement, the transactions contemplated hereby, any provision hereof or the breach, performance, enforcement or validity or invalidity of this Agreement or any provision hereof (and agrees not to commence any suit, action or proceeding relating thereto except in such courts). THE PARTIES HERETO EACH HEREBY KNOWINGLY, VOLUNTARILY AND INTENTIONALLY WAIVE THE RIGHT EACH MAY HAVE TO A TRIAL BY JURY WITH RESPECT TO ANY PROCEEDINGS BASED HEREON, OR ARISING OUT OF, UNDER OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT, OR ANY COURSE OF CONDUCT, COURSE OF DEALING, STATEMENTS (WHETHER ORAL OR WRITTEN) OR ACTIONS OF ANY PARTY TO THIS AGREEMENT. THIS PROVISION IS A MATERIAL INDUCEMENT FOR THE PARTIES TO ENTER INTO THIS AGREEMENT. Inspection of Records. Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Shared Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times. Entire Agreement. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof. Section Headings. The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof. Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument. Several Liability. For the avoidance of doubt, the liability of each of Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V is several and not joint and each of Minco III, Minco IV and Minco V shall be liable only for its obligations (and not the obligations of the other Project Owners) under this Agreement.
